The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Jan. 31: Refusing to allow foreign institutional investors (FIIs) in the debt market, Reserve Bank of India (RBI) deputy governor Rakesh Mohan today said the FII cap on the debt market would continue. ?Some of the cost of high forex reserves is being borne by the tax-payer and allowing FIIs in debt will only increase the burden,? he said.

 Mumbai, Jan. 31: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has banned one, suspended eight and warned 10 brokers for alleged violation of its rules and regulations. The regulator has cancelled the certificate of registration of sub-broker Harvic Management Services affiliated to BM Gandhi Securities.

 Mumbai, Jan. 31: Thermax Ltd will split its shares with a face value of Rs 10 in the ratio of 1:5. The board has approved the split, subject to shareholders? approval. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 31: To tighten the prosecution mechanism against corporate offenders, the government has set up a committee to look into ways to strengthen the Serious Frauds Investigation Office.

 New Delhi, Jan. 31: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (IRDA) has issued a warning for insurers selling keyman insurance cover through endowment or unit-linked plans.




